<h2>Persistant Configuration set event</h2>

This event is used to update persistant configuration.

Type=
Source=variable

<h3>Event Type</h3>
http://id.webbrick.co.uk/events/config/set

<h3>Event Source</h3>
The event type is variable and names the piece of persistant storage, it should follow the form of a relative URI and
may get turned into an absolute URI when it crosses gateway boundaries.

<h3>Other Data</h3>
The payload of the event (other data) is dependant on the event source. generally it will consist of a single simple value, unless
there are a set of codependant values that should be delivered together, in which case it expected that the payload will consist 
of a set of name value pairs that have context within the event source given.

